  "text": "The final aim of this work is to express the rMAbs in the swine enteric tract to examine their protective effect on mucosal surfaces against viral challenge. In these experiments IgA isotype antibodies are known to be more stable than those with the IgG isotype [CITATION_1] . To compare the neutralizing activities of rIgG1 and rIgA, supernatants containing recombinant antibodies at the same titer, as determined by RIA, were used in neutralization assays. Recombinant IgA neutralized TGEV 50-fold more effectively than rIgG1, as expected for a dimeric immunoglobulin (Fig. 3) .",
